Here's a basic example of a chatbot application using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. This chatbot will respond to basic user queries.Here's a basic example of a chatbot application using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. This chatbot will retml*
```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Chatbot</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="chat-container">
        <div class="chat-header">
            <h2>Chatbot</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="chat-body">
            <div class="message-container">
                <div class="message" id="user-message"></div>
                <div class="message" id="bot-message"></div>
            </div>
            <input type="text" id="user-input" placeholder="Type a message...">
            <button id="send-button">Send</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

*style.css*
```
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

.chat-container {
    width: 400px;
    height: 600px;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
    margin: 40px auto;
    padding: 20px;
}

.chat-header {
    background-color: #f0f0f0;
    padding: 10px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc;
}

.chat-body {
    padding: 20px;
}

.message-container {
    padding: 10px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #ccc;
}

.message {
    padding: 10px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    background-color: #f0f0f0;
}

#user-message {
    background-color: #ccc;
}

#bot-message {
    background-color: #0f0;
}

#user-input {
    width: 70%;
    height: 30px;
    padding: 10px;
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
}

#send-button {
    width: 20%;
    height: 30px;
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    color: #fff;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 5px;
    cursor: pointer;
}

#send-button:hover {
    background-color: #3e8e41;
}
```

*script.js*
```
const userMessage = document.getElementById('user-message');
const botMessage = document.getElementById('bot-message');
const userInput = document.getElementById('user-input');
const sendButton = document.getElementById('send-button');

const botResponses = {
    'hello': 'Hi! How can I assist you today?',
    'how are you': 'I\'m doing well, thanks for asking!',
    'what is your purpose': 'I\'m here to provide information and answer your questions to the best of my abilities.',
    'default': 'Sorry, I didn\'t understand that. Can you please rephrase your question?'
};

sendButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const userText = userInput.value.toLowerCase();
    let botText = '';

    if (userText === '') {
        botText = 'Please enter a message.';
    } else if (botResponses[userText]) {
        botText = botResponses[userText];
    } else {
        botText = botResponses['default'];
    }

    userMessage.innerText = userText;
    botMessage.innerText = botText;
    userInput.value = '';
});
```

This code creates a basic chatbot that responds to user input. The chatbot has a predefined set of responses to specific user queries. If the user enters some responses, the chatbot will respond with a default message.

